> user
Implement the `convo.output-tag-execute-shell` command.

Requirements:
- The command should be ran in the bash shell
- The output of the command should be written the the end of the current file wrapped in a XML tag
- Use args.cwd as the working directory for the script. If not defined use the current working directory of the current process.
- Both stdout and stderr should be captured and written back to the current file
- The XML tag should have 1 attribute named script-name populated by args.targetPath
- After the script starts the window should be scrolled to the end of the file

Output Format:
<EXAMPLE_OUTPUT_FORMAT>
/> user

<SCRIPT_OUTPUT script-name="list-frontend-package-content">
``` txt
OUTPUT GOES HERE
```
</SCRIPT_OUTPUT>

</EXAMPLE_OUTPUT_FORMAT>

If the file already ends with `> user` do not add it twice


